The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Sri Lanka okays Pak tour
                                                                                                                                                                                           Sri Lanka okays Pak tour
                      
	Colombo: Sri Lanka Friday decided to go ahead with its cricket tour of Pakistan to fill in for the cancelled India trip, putting an end to the uncertainty over the fate of the series.         
	Sri Lanka president Mahinda Rajapaksa Friday discussed the issue with foreign minister Rohitha Bogollgama, who recommended that the tour should proceed as scheduled from January 20 to February 25.         
	Incidentally, the International Cricket Council (ICC) had said it would carry out an independent security assessment before allowing its match officials to supervise.         
	Addressing a press conference, ICC chief executive officer Haroon Lorgat had said: We will do an independent assessment of the situation there, for the safety of the match officials.         
